Describe an advertisement that you don't like

I’m going to talk about an advertisement that I really don’t like. It’s a commercial that often pops up when I’m watching videos on YouTube, and honestly, I find it quite annoying. I first came across it about three months ago while I was at home watching an English video to practice my listening skills.

The ad is about a type of milk designed for elderly people, which claims to improve bone health and even reduce joint pain in a short time. It features Cát Tường, a well-known TV host in Vietnam, as the brand ambassador. In the video, she talks about her personal experience using the product and says that it helped her significantly, which makes it sound quite convincing at first.

However, what really bothers me is its length and frequency. The ad is unusually long—around four minutes—and it shows up repeatedly, almost every time I click on a new video. Because of that, it interrupts my viewing experience and quickly becomes frustrating.

Another reason I dislike it is that I feel it exaggerates the product’s benefits. I’ve come across several online reviews suggesting that the results are not as effective as advertised. So in a way, it feels a bit misleading, especially for older people who might trust this kind of endorsement.

Overall, this advertisement leaves a negative impression on me. It’s intrusive, repetitive, and not entirely trustworthy. I really hope there will be stricter regulations in the future to control misleading ads like this, so viewers can have a better and more honest online experience.
